OL,3,CFor Indians around the world, Air
OL,4,CIndia's legacy makes the tragedy more
OL,5,Cpainful
OL,7,FFounded in 1932, JRD Tata first named
OL,8,Fit Tata Airlines and then Air India,
OL,9,Fas a pre-independence gift to the
OL,10,Fnation.
OL,12,FJRD Tata was the first pilot, flying
OL,13,Fthe first De Havilland Puss Moth at
OL,14,Fage 25, and making his solo run from
OL,15,FKarachi, which was then a part of
OL,16,FBritish India, to Bombay in 1932.
OL,18,FThis was 15 years before India gained
OL,19,FIndependence from British Rule.
