OL,4,CIndia's legacy makes the tragedy more
OL,5,Cpainful
OL,7,FWhen World War II began in 1939, civil
OL,8,Faviation ceased, and the airline began
OL,9,Frendering exceptional service to the
OL,10,FRoyal Air Force (RAF).
OL,12,FThese aircraft were used for a variety
OL,13,Fof war efforts, including transporting
OL,14,Fwounded military personnel and
OL,15,Frefugees, priority mail, freight and
OL,16,Fcivilian passengers, and overhauling
OL,17,Fand maintaining RAF equipment.
OL,19,FThrough the decades, Air India became
OL,20,Fthe number one South Asian Aviation
OL,21,Fplayer in the international market.
