OL,3,CFor Indians around the world, Air
OL,4,CIndia's legacy makes the tragedy more
OL,5,Cpainful
OL,7,FThe Doors and George Harrison flew on
OL,8,Fthe airline it; and it is said that
OL,9,FSalvador Dali gifted the airline with
OL,10,Fan ashtray designed just for them.
OL,12,FAir India's first commercial flight
OL,13,Ffrom Bombay to London Heathrow was
OL,14,Fcalled the Malabar Princess, and took
OL,15,Foff in 1948.
OL,17,FIn 1953, the Indian Government took
OL,18,Fover the airline and nationalised it,
OL,19,Frunning it with taxpayer money for the
OL,20,Fnext few decades.
