OL,3,CFor Indians around the world, Air
OL,4,CIndia's legacy makes the tragedy more
OL,5,Cpainful
OL,7,FThe airline suffered a further blow
OL,8,Fwhen the Indian aviation industry was
OL,9,Fopened to private airlines in the
OL,10,F1990s. With spiralling debts, it could
OL,11,Fnot compete with up-and-coming
OL,12,Fairlines.
OL,14,FAfter repeated attempts to sell the
OL,15,Fcompany, the Tata group took over Air
OL,16,FIndia for a rough price of #1.7
OL,17,Fbillion in 2023. Indians called this a
OL,18,Fhomecoming - a national emblem
OL,19,Freturning to its original founders
OL,20,Fafter seven decades.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
